        "answer_count": 5,
        "title": "Find a string (or a line) in a txt File Java",
        "body": "<p>let's say I have a txt file containing:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>john\ndani\nzack\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>the user will input a string, for example \"omar\"\nI want the program to search that txt file for the String \"omar\", if it doesn't exist, simply display \"doesn't exist\".<\/p>\n\n<p>I tried the function String.endsWith() or String.startsWith(), but that of course displays \"doesn't exist\" 3 times.<\/p>\n\n<p>I started java only 3 weeks ago, so I am a total newbie...please bear with me.\nthank you.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 20418319,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "string",
            "file"
        ],
        "score": 10,
        "accepted_answer_id": 20418351,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 84520
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f83cc994c98e417a3e0e0971c0480293?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2102673,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1869846,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1869846/ruchira-gayan-ranaweera",
                "reputation": 35683,
                "display_name": "Ruchira Gayan Ranaweera",
                "accept_rate": 56
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 6,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1386316715,
            "creation_date": 1386314552,
            "body": "<p>Just read this text file and put each word in to a <code>List<\/code> and you can check whether that <code>List<\/code> contains your word. <\/p>\n\n<p>You can use <code>Scanner scanner=new Scanner(\"FileNameWithPath\");<\/code> to read file and you can try following to add words to <code>List<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> List&lt;String&gt; list=new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n while(scanner.hasNextLine()){\n     list.add(scanner.nextLine()); \n\n }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Then check your word is there or not<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if(list.contains(\"yourWord\")){\n\n  // found.\n}else{\n // not found\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>BTW you can search directly in file too. <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>while(scanner.hasNextLine()){\n     if(\"yourWord\".equals(scanner.nextLine().trim())){\n        // found\n        break;\n      }else{\n       // not found\n\n      }\n\n }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 20418351,
            "question_id": 20418319,
            "last_edit_date": 1386316715
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/Ivtn0.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 905416,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 940428,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/940428/prabhakaran-ramaswamy",
                "reputation": 26117,
                "display_name": "Prabhakaran Ramaswamy",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1386314563,
            "creation_date": 1386314563,
            "body": "<p>use  <code>String.contains(your search String)<\/code> instead of <code>String.endsWith()<\/code> or <code>String.startsWith()<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>eg<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> str.contains(\"omar\"); \n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 20418355,
            "question_id": 20418319
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/wXAK9.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 1920143,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1731862,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1731862/ankur-shanbhag",
                "reputation": 7804,
                "display_name": "Ankur Shanbhag",
                "accept_rate": 71
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1386314655,
            "creation_date": 1386314655,
            "body": "<p>You can go other way around. <strong>Instead of printing 'does not exist', print 'exists' if match is found<\/strong> while traversing the file and break; If entire file is traversed and no match was found, only then go ahead and display 'does not exist'.<\/p>\n\n<p>Also, use <code>String.contains()<\/code> in place of <code>str.startsWith()<\/code> or <code>str.endsWith()<\/code>. Contains check will search for a match in the entire string and not just at the start or end.<\/p>\n\n<p>Hope it makes sense.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 20418379,
            "question_id": 20418319
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e3d85f265ae23ca51f3f1c5f3744a21a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 3411754,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2862023,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2862023/hitman",
                "reputation": 598,
                "display_name": "Hitman"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1386317629,
            "creation_date": 1386314701,
            "body": "<p>Read the content of the text file: <a href=\"http://www.javapractices.com/topic/TopicAction.do?Id=42\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.javapractices.com/topic/TopicAction.do?Id=42<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>And after that just use the <code>textData.contains(user_input);<\/code> method, where <code>textData<\/code> is the data read from the file, and the <code>user_input<\/code> is the string that is searched by the user<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>UPDATE<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static StringBuilder readFile(String path) \n {       \n        // Assumes that a file article.rss is available on the SD card\n        File file = new File(path);\n        StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder();\n        if (!file.exists()) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"File not found\");\n        }\n        BufferedReader reader = null;\n        try {\n            reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader(file));\n            String line;\n            while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {\n                builder.append(line);\n            }\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            e.printStackTrace();\n        } finally {\n            if (reader != null) {\n                try {\n                    reader.close();\n                } catch (IOException e) {\n                    e.printStackTrace();\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n       return builder;\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This method returns the StringBuilder created from the data you have read from the text file given as parameter.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can see if the user input string is in the file like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>int index = readFile(filePath).indexOf(user_input);\n        if ( index &gt; -1 )\n            System.out.println(\"exists\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 20418394,
            "question_id": 20418319,
            "last_edit_date": 1386317629
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/etgjJ.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 3835277,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 3179759,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3179759/alex-glasseditor-com",
                "reputation": 15627,
                "display_name": "Alex - GlassEditor.com"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1537339211,
            "creation_date": 1537339211,
            "body": "<p>You can do this with <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/10/docs/api/java/nio/file/Files.html#lines(java.nio.file.Path)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Files.lines<\/code><\/a>:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>try(Stream&lt;String&gt; lines = Files.lines(Paths.get(\"...\")) ) {\n    if(lines.anyMatch(\"omar\"::equals)) {\n  //or lines.anyMatch(l -&gt; l.contains(\"omar\"))\n        System.out.println(\"found\");\n    } else {\n        System.out.println(\"not found\");\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Note that it uses the UTF-8 charset to read the file, if that's not what you want you can pass your charset as the second argument to <code>Files.lines<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 52399635,
            "question_id": 20418319
        }
